  "title": "Operations Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>The Role</strong><br />As an Operations Executive, you will be the bridge between high-level strategy and daily execution. You will oversee day-to-day workflows, manage resources, and implement process improvements to ensure our organisation runs at peak efficiency.<br /><br /><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong><br />- <strong>Daily Management</strong>: Oversee daily business operations and ensure all activities align with organizational goals and timelines.<br />- <strong>Process Optimization</strong>: Identify bottlenecks and implement new workflows or technologies to improve productivity and reduce operational costs.<br />- <strong>Stakeholder Coordination</strong> : Act as a primary liaison between management and various departments (e.g., HR, Finance, IT) to ensure seamless communication.<br />- <strong>Data & Reporting</strong>: Track key performance indicators (KPIs) and prepare detailed reports for senior management to guide strategic decision-making.<br />- <strong>Compliance & Safety</strong>: Ensure all operations comply with company policies, industry regulations, and safety standards.<br />- <strong>Resource Allocation</strong>: Manage manpower, equipment, and budgets effectively to meet project requirements.<br /><br /><strong>Requirements</strong><br />- <strong>Experience </strong>: Minimum of 1-2 years of experience in an operations or administrative role.<br />- <strong>Skills </strong>: Strong analytical and problem-solving skills to handle complex operational challenges. Exceptional interpersonal and communication skills to lead teams and work with diverse stakeholders. Proficiency in Microsoft Office Suite (especially Excel) and operational software. High level of adaptability and resilience in a fast-paced environment.<br /><br /><strong>Why Join Us?</strong><br />- Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses.<br />- Comprehensive medical and dental benefits.<br />- Clear career progression paths toward Operations Management.<br />- A collaborative and inclusive company culture.<br /><br /><strong>Job Details:</strong><br />- Location: Singapore<br />- Salary: $3,000/month<br />- Job Type: Full-time<br />- Working Hours: Monday to Friday, 9am to 6pm</p>",
